This paper discusses the impact of hardware faults on the accuracy of DNNs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel error mitigation technique using clipped activation functions, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the resilience of DNNs, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.AR).
